The Tanzanian nationals were being transported by Home Affairs officials from Durban to Johannesburg when they broke out of a van as it approached the Mooi River toll plaza.Home Affairs provincial manager Cyril Mncwabe said two vehicles with two officials each were transporting 13 immigrants to the Lindela Repatriation Centre a detention centre for undocumented migrants for possible deportation when five escaped from the one vehicle.After a massive manhunt involving police the farming community in the KwaZulu-Natal midlands and three private aircraft from the KwaZulu-Natal Honorary Officers the men were eventually apprehended by police."One of the men was injured and taken to hospital under police guard. The others were taken to the Mooi River police station and will be transported to Johannesburg."No criminal case has been opened " said Mncwabe.